The article is a press briefing on President Obama's upcoming trip to Russia, Italy, and Africa. The President will have meetings with leaders in each country and address various issues such as U.S.-Russia relations, climate change, and governance in Africa. In Moscow, the President will discuss a range of topics, including the START treaty and energy issues. In Italy, he will attend the G8 summit and discuss economic recovery, climate change, and other global issues. In Ghana, the President will emphasize the importance of governance and meet with Ghanaian leaders to discuss development, regional stability, and other issues. The President's trip aims to advance U.S. national security goals and strengthen relationships with key countries.